│ Understanding the Issue: The crash occurs in                                │
│ SystemZTTIImpl::getCastInstrCost when it encounters a cast instruction      │
│ where the source type is scalar (i32) but the destination type is vector    │
│ (<4 x i32>). The assertion `!Dst->isVectorTy()` fails because the SystemZ   │
│ TTI implementation assumes that when the source is not a vector, the        │
│ destination should also not be a vector. However, this assumption is        │
│ incorrect - LLVM supports casts from scalar to vector types (like zext i32  │
│ to <4 x i32>), which are valid IR constructs.\n\n2. Analyzing `opt`'s Log:  │
│ The debug log shows that the SLP vectorizer is trying to vectorize a bundle │
│ of zext instructions: `%42 = zext <4 x i1> %41 to <4 x i32>`, etc. When     │
│ calculating the cost for this tree, it calls getCastInstrCost with          │
│ Opcode=39 (ZExt), SrcTy=i1 (scalar), and DstTy=<4 x i32> (vector). This     │
│ triggers the assertion failure in the SystemZ TTI implementation.\n\n3.     │
│ Root Cause Analysis: The SystemZ TTI implementation has an overly           │
│ restrictive assertion that assumes non-vector sources must have non-vector  │
│ destinations. However, LLVM's IR allows casting from scalar to vector       │
│ types, and the SLP vectorizer legitimately creates such patterns during     │
│ vectorization. The assertion should be removed or replaced with proper      │
│ handling of scalar-to-vector casts.\n\n4. Proposed Edit Point(s): The       │
│ assertion on line 783 in SystemZTargetTransformInfo.cpp is too restrictive  │
│ and should be removed. The code already has a branch for handling vector    │
│ types (`else if (ST->hasVector())` starting at line 845), but the current   │
│ logic prevents reaching that branch when Src is scalar but Dst is vector.   │
│ By removing this assertion, the function can fall through to the base class │
│ implementation which can handle scalar-to-vector casts properly.\n\n5.      │
│ Conclusion: Removing the assertion will allow the SystemZ TTI to handle     │
│ scalar-to-vector cast cost queries correctly, preventing the crash while    │
│ maintaining correct cost modeling. The base class implementation            │
│ (BaseT::getCastInstrCost) already handles these cases appropriately."})     │
